text.section:
The annual report shall include the following information:
The number and ages of children who received hearing aids through the Program that year;
The number of children who received hearing aids through the Program that year and subsequently received hearing aids through Medicaid, the Maryland Children's Health Program, or private insurance;
The length of each original loan;
The number of times that each original loan was extended and the length of each extension;
The number of times that hearing aids were not properly returned to the Loan Bank; and
Any other information that the State Superintendent believes is relevant to evaluating the costs and benefits of the Program.
